---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About — Real Caffeine Calculator"
  description="Real Caffeine Calculator is a free browser-based tool that shows you exactly how much caffeine is in your body right now, and when it's safe to sleep."
  canonical="https://realcaffeinecalculator.com/about"
>

<section style="padding: 72px 24px 96px;">
  <div style="max-width: 640px; margin: 0 auto;">

    <p style="font-size: 12px; font-weight: 500; color: #555; letter-spacing: 0.6px; text-transform: uppercase; font-family: 'Courier New', monospace; margin-bottom: 20px;">
      About
    </p>

    <h1 style="font-size: 36px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -1.4px; color: #fff; line-height: 1.1; margin-bottom: 32px;">
      What is Real Caffeine Calculator?
    </h1>

    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 20px;">
      <p style="font-size: 16px; color: #888; line-height: 1.75;">
        Real Caffeine Calculator is a free, browser-based tool that uses the scientific caffeine half-life formula to show you exactly how much caffeine is circulating in your bloodstream at any given moment. Log your drinks, set your bedtime, and see a live decay chart — no account, no app, no tracking.
      </p>
      <p style="font-size: 16px; color: #888; line-height: 1.75;">
        The calculator supports drinks from Starbucks, Dunkin', energy drinks like Bang and Monster, home-brewed coffee, teas, and custom inputs. It accounts for multiple drinks consumed at different times and sizes, summing their independent decay curves to give you an accurate total.
      </p>
      <p style="font-size: 16px; color: #888; line-height: 1.75;">
        It's built for anyone who cares about sleep quality, athletic recovery, or simply wants to make smarter decisions about when to have that next cup. The science is straightforward: caffeine has a 5-hour half-life in most adults, and keeping your bedtime level below 50mg gives your body the best shot at restful sleep.
      </p>

      <div class="key-facts-box" style="
        margin-top: 12px;
        padding: 20px 24px;
        background: #0d0d0d;
        border: 1px solid #1a1a1a;
        border-radius: 12px;
      ">
        <p style="font-size: 13px; font-weight: 500; color: #555; margin-bottom: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px; font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;">
          Key facts
        </p>
        <ul style="list-style: none; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 10px;">
          {[
            'Caffeine half-life: 5 hours for most healthy adults',
            'Sleep-safe threshold: 50mg remaining',
            'FDA daily limit: 400mg',
            'All calculation runs in your browser — no data is sent anywhere',
            'No sign-up, no tracking, completely free',
          ].map(fact => (
            <li style="display: flex; gap: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #888; align-items: flex-start;">
              <span style="color: #2e7d32; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 1px;">✓</span>
              <span>{fact}</span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>

      <p style="font-size: 14px; color: #555; line-height: 1.7; margin-top: 8px;">
        This tool is for informational purposes only and does not constitute medical advice. If you have concerns about caffeine sensitivity, heart conditions, or sleep disorders, consult a healthcare professional.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div style="margin-top: 48px; padding-top: 32px; border-top: 1px solid #111;">
      <a href="/" style="
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 8px;
        height: 44px;
        padding: 0 20px;
        background: #fff;
        color: #000;
        border-radius: 9999px;
        font-size: 14px;
        font-weight: 500;
        letter-spacing: -0.2px;
        transition: opacity 0.15s;
      " onmouseover="this.style.opacity='0.88'" onmouseout="this.style.opacity='1'">
        Open the calculator →
      </a>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

</Layout>
